    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 22,
        "summary": "A good name is better than riches\u2014Train up a child in the way he should go.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "A good name is rather to be chosen than great riches, and loving favour rather than silver and gold.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 7:1; 1\u00a0Ne. 1:1.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The rich and poor meet together: the Lord is the maker of them all.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:19.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A prudent man foreseeth the evil, and hideth himself: but the simple pass on, and are punished.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "By humility and the fear of the Lord are riches, and honour, and life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thorns and snares are in the way of the froward: he that doth keep his soul shall be far from them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0perverse.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Train up a child in the way he should go: and when he is old, he will not depart from it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:4 (1\u20134). TG\u00a0Education; Family, Children, Responsibilities toward; Marriage, Fatherhood; Teaching.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The rich ruleth over the poor, and the borrower is servant to the lender.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 19:35.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Borrow; Debt.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that soweth iniquity shall reap vanity: and the rod of his anger shall fail.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:16.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Harvest.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hath a bountiful eye shall be blessed; for he giveth of his bread to the poor.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bread.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Almsgiving.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Cast out the scorner, and contention shall go out; yea, strife and reproach shall cease.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that loveth pureness of heart, for the grace of his lips the king shall be his friend.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The eyes of the Lord preserve knowledge, and he overthroweth the words of the transgressor.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The slothful man saith, There is a lion without, I shall be slain in the streets.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 835
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The mouth of strange women is a deep pit: he that is abhorred of the Lord shall fall therein.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fornication.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Foolishness is bound in the heart of a child; but the rod of correction shall drive it far from him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that oppresseth the poor to increase his riches, and he that giveth to the rich, shall surely come to want.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Oppression.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Bow down thine ear, and hear the words of the wise, and apply thine heart unto my knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it is a pleasant thing if thou keep them within thee; they shall withal be fitted in thy lips.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "That thy trust may be in the Lord, I have made known to thee this day, even to thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Have not I written to thee excellent things in counsels and knowledge,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That I might make thee know the certainty of the words of truth; that thou mightest answer the words of truth to them that send unto thee?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 18:3; 98:11.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Rob not the poor, because he is poor: neither oppress the afflicted in the gate:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 7:10.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the Lord will plead their cause, and spoil the soul of those that spoiled them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 35:10; Prov. 23:11.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 124:75.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Make no friendship with an angry man; and with a furious man thou shalt not go:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Friendship.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lest thou learn his ways, and get a snare to thy soul.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not thou one of them that strike hands, or of them that are sureties for debts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0shake hands, showing agreement.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 6:1; 11:15.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If thou hast nothing to pay, why should he take away thy bed from under thee?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Remove not the ancient landmark, which thy fathers have set.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 19:14; Job 24:2; Prov. 23:10; Hosea 5:10.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Seest thou a man diligent in his business? he shall stand before kings; he shall not stand before mean men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Diligence.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}